  <mainDescription>Project Sponsor &quot;owns&quot; the project and has the ultimate responsibility for seeing that the intended benefits are realized&#xD;
to create the value forecast in the business case. Project Sponsor facilitates the necessary organizational support needed&#xD;
to make strategic decisions and create a successful project. Project Sponsor escalates project issues and risks effectively&#xD;
at the organizational and executive levels. This includes decisions on changes, risks, conflicting objectives and any other&#xD;
issue that is outside of the project manager's designated authority.</mainDescription>
  <skills>Understand business cases, corporate strategy and business requirements. Executive level communication skills .&#xD;
Organiational negotiator and project cheerleader. Executive and board level confidence.</skills>
  <assignmentApproaches>Sponsor must have the authority to accept or avoid project risks.</assignmentApproaches>
  <synonyms>Executive, Partner , Owner</synonyms>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
